ayant este pour quelque jours hors dela ville, a mon retour j'ay trouva la vre
agreable du 16 cor., & ensuite de vostre ordre je vous envoyerez avecq la pre
bazque sui Brussel a mad. caros le drap a la mode, avecq les perpetuanet
& la baye blanches, & je medere avecq demy drap rouge, selon l'eschantillion
que vous m'avez, & je tachere de faire, mon debvoir pour vous plaire, entre
temps tous nostres marchandises sont arrive a Brugges, pour moy environ
20 pacques, dont vous avez vre part des eschantillion, ils seront icy environ
le fine de semaine prochaine, si en cas que je vous peu rendre service, commde

Rijssel Richard Southell
In answer to yo oft 18 curtt. find inclosed a bill for £80- att the charge
of Pieter de ka, adressed by michiel vanden Cruyce, whicht is past due, except
the 6 dayes, so you must demand payment upon rceipt here of & pass to
mij acctt., I am returned from Brussel much frustrated of my exspetat
for there was little or no mony for my mee, and I had & have monyes
to paij & though I do butt vere little for H.C. yett he draws not the
less, & I can not suster to redraw on our ex. & I wuld remitt to
other from in my own bills on him, butt, that he doth not love, ie
must have patience oter wist should have remtted you more wich yu
may excpecct another time, for you may considder wch debtes come in so 23
slow by with you, & little to do how itt sange here, for i bellave yo trade &
mony ought to be at quick againe as ours which I could wish suceeded in all
respects to yo. content
In Antwerp 25 Juny

Sr. mj last to you was on the 18: curitt: sence non from you thomas smith is well
arrived butt I know not as yett, what goods you have shipt for mee on his board
John Collinier is also on this side, butt of white is no news: you will do well
to dispatch a pack of frise as formelly desired, besides one pack of 12 halve
white cottons from 24 a 25„ pence a goad, besides one pack, to cont. 4
of £11:10 a £12 a peece of the deepest cullour to be hadd 3 p. reds of £9: & 3 of
£10: a peece or there about to them 10 peeces would desire you to add 2 green
clothes, such as you are used to send JV. of Brussels of which inclosed a pattarn
I supose they come about 4:6 pence ayd which you will know best & lett them
10 reds & 2 green be made up in one pack & sended forwards pr. first lett mee
have good substantiall goods inclosed remitt you £101: att the charge of
gabriel de la porte 2 uso att 35:5 for ijd acctt. for which please to procure the
needfull, & pass to acctt. accordingly. I long to heare from you & hope the b.N
silver marck stuck cloathes maij be readij: I peeters, is dead, I know no remedie
except mr slaughter takes againe the goods & what comes short maij be formd in
mony, which is the need full att present from

Sr. my last to you was on the 18. curitt sence recd. yd of 6 & 10 ditto: thamas smith
is also wel arrived thanckes be god, now Richd pindar is att Hull lett all the
kersies come with him & some cloaths the rest with nelson, which is departed
for that please, place bij this time, as yett I have non of the goods, because
of some hindrance of the waters from bruges to gant which I hope
will be remedied suddenly you please also to in order m.potter the providing
of a pack to containe & wit white grayes long cloathes from 3 st 8 pene
to 4:8 pence a yard raw them 8 peeces to be one pack by itt self wrapped with
2 or 3 white manchester bayes butt recommand him that these whites must
be well lained, and not full of great spotts, which happens oftend by the
worckmens negligence, in so much that our last wee. had have been some times
Returned because theij were not cleane on the rong side as well as within the
cloths so he must take especiall care to send pure goods and peiworths them
all to be well handled & curiously toilledted: in closed remitt ijon £100: att the charge
of robert breton of 23:h curitt 3 weekes after date, besides £40: on John Cannon
att 8 dayes sight for boath which please to procure the needfull & pass to my
accompt. I have been att Brussell & provided the needfull to compleat yd. ordered
laces: truly I promise mij self much of them because, mee thinckes I never had
the likes you shall have them aboard John colluier & invoyces p. next
went away hope him well arrived of which I should be gladd to have yd advise
London Henry Collier

S. have before mee yd of 27:th past. & 1o curitt yd bill of £100: is accepted & past
£70: to mine & 30 to yd acctt. I have asso accepted yd bill for £110: for yd acctts
& when yd. bill for £50 or John button shall be paijd, shall be noted, in yd creditt
side pray spare mee with yd draughts. yds bale N:38 is arrived att bruges & should
have been here bj this time, had not some thing happaned to the po waters in
the canael between Gant & bruges hindred itt, which now I supose is
remedied, so that no others could pass. itt is now the deadest time for trade
of all the yeare, so that wee have no vent, butt hope within a month that
itt will come in againe. att least wee gott the sentence insimated to TH
him self which hath reformed and appelled att a higher count, I was yeasterday
with his layer, which not knowing that I knew of the concernes told mee, that
